Negative Reviews:
-Staff showed no personal interest in their guest. There was no special treatment for Riu Class members, no points nor compensation whatsoever (so what’s the use?) Even though Riu class website promises you all kind of additional services. On my birthday the hotel made no effort on it’s own to recognize my birthday;
-The swimming pool is more like an ice cold water bath. It’s definitely not for swimming anyway;
The fitness area is too small and has limited options for the amount of guests the hotel receives;
-Room 1044 does not have a nice view. 
-Guests are continuously asked to sanitize their hands with alcohol, which is bad for you health, while you can easily wash your hands with soap and water nearby, which is more safe and clean. In the meanwhile the staff lays downs the cutlery and cleans the tables with their bare hands(?);
-Food menu on rooftop bar only offers limited options. 
-As we like to sleep in during vacation, it’s disappointing that breakfast is only served till 10.30(/11.00 during Weekends);
